The hollowness you feel is just becoming an adult and realizing, that there is no such thing as "fulfillment" or "closure".

Life is just a repeating cycle of your cells dying and replicating, while your brain tries to convince you that your existence has meaning. You will never be able to fill that void, because that is just the human condition. 
Always wanting to reach a goal and waiting for happiness, fulfillment or closure, and every time you reach a goal, you get a burst of dopamine, and then it fades into nothing. 
The happiness hormones get flushed out of your system through your kidneys and liver, and then you'll want to find something else you can work towards. 

What I realized is, you don't need to fill that void. You just have to accept that you are human, and this is how your nervous system keeps you alive. The reason why people don't talk about this is, because it's scary having to accept the feeling of emptiness and meaninglessness.

Hope this gives you another perspective you can think through! :3
